news_header: Deepseek leaked user data; cooperating with South Korean authorities.
news_text: In South Korea, authorities confirmed that Chinese AI company Deepseek leaked user information to a third party. Deepseek sent data to Bytedance, the owner of TikTok. The South Korean Safety Authority has not disclosed the extent of the leak. Deepseek admitted to compliance issues with local data protection laws and is willing to cooperate with the South Korean Data Protection Authority. The company recently announced a new AI model, R1, which competes closely with US models.
